  "chapter": {
    "number": 62,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Waiting on God"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "hebrew_subtitle",
        "content": [
          "For the choirmaster. According to Jeduthun. A Psalm of David."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In God alone my soul finds rest;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "my salvation comes from Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He alone is my rock and my salvation.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He is my fortress;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will never be shaken.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How long will you threaten a man?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Will all of you throw him down",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "like a leaning wall",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or a tottering fence?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They fully intend to cast him down from his lofty perch;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they delight in lies;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "with their mouths they bless,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but inwardly they curse.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "Selah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rest in God alone, O my soul,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for my hope comes from Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He alone is my rock and my salvation;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He is my fortress; I will not be shaken.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My salvation and my honor rest on God, my strong rock;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "my refuge is in God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Trust in Him at all times, O people;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "pour out your hearts before Him.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "God is our refuge.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "Selah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Lowborn men are but a vapor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the exalted but a lie.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Weighed on the scale, they go up;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "together they are but a vapor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Place no trust in extortion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or false hope in stolen goods.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "If your riches increase,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not set your heart upon them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "God has spoken once;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have heard this twice:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "that power belongs to God,",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "and loving devotion to You, O Lord.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For You will repay each man",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "according to his deeds.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4413
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
